  "text": "The relationship between user behaviour during the dwell time on the search engine results page and relevancy of the page was investigated in [CITATION_1] . The experiments showed that including cursor movements and scrolling, was more effective than considering only the dwell time, in order to estimate the page (document) relevancy. Similarly, in [CITATION_2] the search performance was enhanced significantly using text-selection data. User post-click behaviour parameters such as mouse clicks, mouse movements, text selection and cursor trails were used to cluster the users based on their behaviour similarity as described in [CITATION_3] .",
